[Patient] "How much water should I drink in a day?"
[Healthcare Educator] "Try to drink about 8 cups of water daily to stay hydrated."
[Patient] "Can I still have my favorite soda?"
[Healthcare Educator] "It's best to limit sugary drinks like soda and opt for water or herbal teas instead."
[Patient] "What about fruit juices, are they okay?"
[Healthcare Educator] "Fruit juices can be high in sugar, so it's better to eat whole fruits and drink water."
[Patient] "I love salty snacks, can I still have them?"
[Healthcare Educator] "It's important to limit salty snacks to help manage your heart failure symptoms better."
[Patient] "What can I drink to stay hydrated besides water?"
[Healthcare Educator] "You can try unsweetened herbal teas or infused water with fruits for a refreshing alternative."